#

# domain routing, SanDiego.NCR.COM acts	as a virtual machine that encompasses
# all of the users in the domain.  In other words, if you know the full	name

pyramid.entry:
#N	pyramid
#F	uunet.uu.net
#O	Pyramid	Technology Corporation
#S	Pyramid	9825; dualPort OSx 5.0d
#C	Stan Portner
#E	postmaster@pyramid.com,	usenet@pyramid.com
#T	+1 408 428 9000
#P	3860 N 1st St, San Jose	CA, 95134
#L	37 25 09 N / 122 04 31 W
#U	amdahl ctnews decwrl epimass infmx leadsv octopus
#U	oliveb oracle nsc prls thirdi triada voder weitek xilinx
#W	sportner@pyramid.com (Stan Portner);Thu	Mar 12 15:28:13	PST 1992
#R	$Revision: 1.12	$ $Date: 91/7/13 $ $Author: news $
#
# We are in the	process	of switching services over to our new internet
# gossip.pyramid.com.  In the end, pyramid.pyramid.com will be aliased
# to gossip.pyramid.com.  Watch	this space for details.
#
# Our USENET feeds are decwrl, oliveb, prls, and amdahl. The #U	entry above
# shows	only full news links; many "alt" only, partial,	local, and regional
# connections also exist.
#
# pyramid.com is the gateway for all Pyramid Technology	Corporation machines;
#
#	user@pyramid.com
# or
#	user@pyrhost.pyramid.com
#
# should get you to anyone. A number of	Pyramid	field offices and support
# groups also have machines on the UUCP	net; each of these is individually
# administered.
#
# The costs below are generally	scaled against what we have to pay for them.
# Small	bonuses	are awarded for	2400bps	or a Telebit. X.25 sites do *not*
# get a	bonus, since in	the US it is more expensive than the telephone.
#
pyramid	.pyramid.com
pyramid	=	pyramid.com
#
# We show the following	internet gateway links to reserve their	names and
# to show that links between them do exist.  When the gateway switchover is
# is complete, the link	cost will drop to a reasonbale cost.
#
pyramid	gossip(WEEKLY),	bertha(WEEKLY)
gossip =	gossip.pyramid.com
bertha =	bertha.pyramid.com
#
# Pyramid's own	field offices. Our internal (hidden) map makes these links much
# cheaper, so we pay for our own mail as much as possible, but the world at
# large	gets the true values.
#
pyramid	!pta(DEMAND+100), pyrbos (DEMAND+100), pyrchi(DEMAND+100),
	pyrdc(DEMAND+75), pyritan(DEMAND+50), pyrla(DEMAND+50),
	pyrnj(DEMAND+50), pyror(DIRECT), pyrtor(DEMAND+100),
	pyrltd(EVENING)
#
# Local	calls from Mountain View -- includes most of Silicon Valley. Ames is
# artificially high because they list a	lot of their Internet connections on
# their	UUCP map, which	throws off our paths; they're actually one of the most
# reliable sites in the	Bay Area.
#
#
